	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How to decode Famicom RF into AV, if I remember correctly: Import an American VCR with a tuner, and connect it to a TV that supports NTSC through AV output. You should be able to see its menus on the TV. Set it to "standard cable" and look around in channels 95-99 for the Famicom video signal, as that's where channels 1 and 2 are stashed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
